{"id":14881631,"mediaExerciseId":"812ed3b9-af82-438f-805c-eaab16fe1df5","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"18","chapterTitle":"Short-Term Finance and Planning","groupId":612437,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":631,"solutions":[{"id":5990681,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires to determine if it is possible for a firm’s cash cycle to be longer than its operating cycle.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f2a28acd0313f70bd8c0a540895b1e11/9966a0ecf18ba3c42b88592849f669d0/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f2a28acd0313f70bd8c0a540895b1e11/9966a0ecf18ba3c42b88592849f669d0/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"It is **not possible** for  for a firm’s cash cycle to be longer than its operating cycle because cash cycle is equal to the operating cycle less accounts payable period.Furthermore, a negative accounts payable period is not possible because it implies that the company pays its bills before they are incurred.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f2a28acd0313f70bd8c0a540895b1e11/60d6357562073103945c4e623029e51c/lateximg_large.png","width":1020},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f2a28acd0313f70bd8c0a540895b1e11/60d6357562073103945c4e623029e51c/lateximg.png","width":511}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"449abc6d-a196-4b74-ac82-e0533bdcb07b","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2},{"id":6403027,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this question, we will discuss whether or not it is conceivable for a company's cash cycle to be much longer than its operational cycle.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The number of days necessary for a company to acquire inventory, sell the inventory, and earn cash from the sale of the inventory is referred to as an **Operating Cycle**.\n\n\n**Cash conversion cycle**, is a statistic that represents the amount of time, in days, that it takes for a corporation to transform its resources into cash flows.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"So, the cash conversion cycle denotes the investment in working capital excluding the payables timespan. The collection period cannot be lengthier than the operating period if indeed the payables duration is favorable. However, the net working capital might well be longer unless commodities are difficult to obtain. \n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"As more than just a matter of fact, the business organization would need to stockpile a sizable quantity of materials. Foremost, the processing time may very well be extended.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"aa10de79-5bb0-426d-a0be-03f1e9af8087","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881632,"exerciseName":"6","page":631,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d478563e-d35d-4027-b2ad-977108886f3b","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-critical-thinking-questions-6-d478563e-d35d-4027-b2ad-977108886f3b"},{"id":14881633,"exerciseName":"7","page":631,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ca0c40b5-750b-4593-97aa-2a78d07e8afa","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-critical-thinking-questions-7-ca0c40b5-750b-4593-97aa-2a78d07e8afa"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881630,"exerciseName":"4","page":631,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"41ded766-1bfd-4359-9be3-005b41225570","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-critical-thinking-questions-4-41ded766-1bfd-4359-9be3-005b41225570"},{"id":14881629,"exerciseName":"3","page":631,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"8d3fc3a8-18d9-4e38-bf8e-94074f7deb3c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-critical-thinking-questions-3-8d3fc3a8-18d9-4e38-bf8e-94074f7deb3c"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-critical-thinking-questions-5-812ed3b9-af82-438f-805c-eaab16fe1df5"}